    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-28T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-28T14:00:00-05:00" n="250"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 661.939/7</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-28T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 28, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName>Warner</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d250fn2">
                        <persName>Langdon Warner</persName>, Vice Consul at Harbin.</note>
                    telegraphs that there is great need of food in the Priamur <pb facs="0229"
                        n="179" xml:id="pg_179"/> and says investigation shows it impossible for
                    food to fall into the hands of the enemy when shipped to that region.</p>
                <p>The American Government would be glad to see the embargo lifted from food
                    shipments to Priamur. The Department has received no reply to its telegrams of
                    May 1 to Tokyo, London, and Paris concerning embargo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
